, and many code paths calling `OpenRepository()` multiple times (e.g., `SaveStep` → helper → helper), you're:\\n- Throwing away the LRU object cache each time (so objects fetched in one call get re-decoded in the next)\\n- Paying ~3 syscalls × N redundant times per operation\\n\\n**Verdict:** The open itself is cheap (~microseconds), but **passing `*git.Repository` down is still worthwhile** for two reasons:\\n\\n1. **LRU cache sharing** — This is the bigger win. When you open once and pass it down, git objects (commits, trees, blobs) decoded during the first operation are cached and reused. With separate opens, each gets a fresh empty 96 MiB LRU, so the same commit/tree objects get re-decoded from packfiles repeatedly.\\n\\n2. **Syscall reduction** — Minor but cumulative, especially in hot paths like hooks where latency matters.\\n\\nI'd suggest starting with the hot paths (hooks, `SaveStep`, rewind) where the same `*git.Repository` is opened 3-5+ times within a single operation. Want me to look at which call chains would benefit most?\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":497,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":55176,\"output_tokens\":666,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":497,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYSMxFe6zXZrHUUJmn3QP\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"8185255e-acb2-452d-b7a9-e62051291a38\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-24T05:44:09.112Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8185255e-acb2-452d-b7a9-e62051291a38\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"408b8c7a-970e-44d6-97d2-5055b778a417\",\"version\":\"2.1.42\",\"gitBranch\":\"commit_optimizations\",\"slug\":\"greedy-crunching-rabbit\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"